## Summary: RSS Feed Implementation in Amytis

I've found and analyzed all RSS feed-related files in the project. Here's the complete overview:

### Core RSS Files

#### 1. **RSS Route Handler** (`/Users/hutusi/workspace/ai/naive/amytis-claude-review/src/app/feed.xml/route.ts`)

```typescript
import { getAllPosts } from '@/lib/markdown';
import { siteConfig } from '../../../site.config';
import { resolveLocale } from '@/lib/i18n';
import { getPostUrl } from '@/lib/urls';

export const dynamic = 'force-static';

export async function GET() {
  const posts = getAllPosts();
  const baseUrl = siteConfig.baseUrl;

  const rssItemsXml = posts
    .map((post) => {
      const url = `${baseUrl}${getPostUrl(post)}`;
      return `
        <item>
          <title><![CDATA[${post.title}]]></title>
          <link>${url}</link>
          <guid>${url}</guid>
          <pubDate>${new Date(post.date).toUTCString()}</pubDate>
          <description><![CDATA[${post.excerpt}]]></description>
          ${post.tags ? post.tags.map(tag => `<category>${tag}</category>`).join('') : ''}
        </item>`;
    })
    .join('');

  const rssXml = `<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom">
  <channel>
    <title><![CDATA[${resolveLocale(siteConfig.title)}]]></title>
    <link>${baseUrl}</link>
    <description><![CDATA[${resolveLocale(siteConfig.description)}]]></description>
    <language>en</language>
    <lastBuildDate>${new Date().toUTCString()}</lastBuildDate>
    <atom:link href="${baseUrl}/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" />
    ${rssItemsXml}
  </channel>
</rss>`;

  return new Response(rssXml, {
    headers: {
      'Content-Type': 'application/xml',
    },
  });
}
```

**Key features:**
- Routes to `/feed.xml` endpoint (Next.js App Router)
- Uses `force-static` dynamic mode for static generation
- Fetches all posts using `getAllPosts()` from markdown library
- Generates RSS 2.0 format with Atom namespace
- Includes post title, link, GUID, pub date, excerpt, and tags
- Uses CDATA sections for safe XML escaping
- Respects `baseUrl` from site config for absolute URLs
- Uses `getPostUrl()` helper to generate correct post URLs

#### 2. **RSS Feed Widget Component** (`/Users/hutusi/workspace/ai/naive/amytis-claude-review/src/components/RssFeedWidget.tsx`)

```typescript
'use client';

import { useState } from 'react';
import { siteConfig } from '../../site.config';
import { LuCopy, LuCheck } from 'react-icons/lu';

export default function RssFeedWidget() {
  const [copied, setCopied] = useState(false);
  const feedUrl = `${siteConfig.baseUrl.replace(/\/+$/, '')}/feed.xml`;

  const handleCopy = async () => {
    try {
      await navigator.clipboard.writeText(feedUrl);
      setCopied(true);
      setTimeout(() => setCopied(false), 2000);
    } catch {
      // clipboard API not available
    }
  };

  return (
    <div className="flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-2.5 my-4 rounded-lg bg-muted/5 border border-muted/15 not-prose">
      <code className="text-xs font-mono text-muted/60 flex-1 truncate">{feedUrl}</code>
      <button
        onClick={handleCopy}
        className="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs text-muted/60 hover:text-accent transition-colors"
        aria-label="Copy feed URL"
      >
        {copied
          ? <><LuCheck className="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-accent" /><span className="text-accent">Copied!</span></>
          : <><LuCopy className="w-3.5 h-3.5" /><span>Copy</span></>
        }
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

**Key features:**
- Client-side component (React hook for copy state)
- Displays feed URL in formatted code block
- Copy-to-clipboard functionality with visual feedback
- Accessible button with aria-label
- Responsive design with Tailwind CSS

#### 3. **MarkdownRenderer Integration** (referenced in `/Users/hutusi/workspace/ai/naive/amytis-claude-review/src/components/MarkdownRenderer.tsx`)

```typescript
// Line 133
const allComponents = { ...components, 'rss-feed': () => <RssFeedWidget /> } as any;
```

This allows MDX/Markdown content to embed the RSS widget using `<rss-feed />` tag.

### Configuration References

#### 4. **Site Config** (`/Users/hutusi/workspace/ai/naive/amytis-claude-review/site.config.ts`)

- **Line 77**: Footer link `{ name: "RSS Feed", url: "/feed.xml", weight: 3 }`
- **Line 36**: Uses `siteConfig.baseUrl` for absolute feed URL generation

### Internationalization Support

#### 5. **Translations** (`/Users/hutusi/workspace/ai/naive/amytis-claude-review/src/i18n/translations.ts`)

**English (lines 31, 93-94):**
```typescript
rss_feed: "RSS Feed",
rss_readers: "RSS Readers",
rss_description: "Subscribe with any RSS reader for automatic updates when new content is published.",
```

**Chinese (lines 163, 225-226):**
```typescript
rss_feed: "RSS 订阅",
rss_readers: "RSS 阅读器",
rss_description: "通过 RSS 阅读器订阅，发布新内容时自动获取更新。",
```

### E2E Tests

#### 6. **Test Coverage** (`/Users/hutusi/workspace/ai/naive/amytis-claude-review/tests/e2e/navigation.test.ts`, lines 43-50)

```typescript
test("feed.xml should exist", async () => {
  if (!(await isServerRunning())) return;

  const response = await fetch(`${BASE_URL}/feed.xml`);
  expect(response.status).toBe(200);
  const text = await response.text();
  expect(text).toContain("<rss");
});
```

### Build Configuration

#### 7. **Next.js Config** (`/Users/hutusi/workspace/ai/naive/amytis-claude-review/next.config.ts`)

- **Line 9**: `output: "export"` - Static export mode enables RSS route to be pre-rendered
- **Line 8**: `trailingSlash: true` - Results in `/feed.xml/` with trailing slash in output

### How It Works

1. **Build Time**: When running `bun run build`, the feed.xml route is statically generated as part of the export
2. **Content Source**: Fetches all posts from `content/posts/` via `getAllPosts()` function
3. **URL Generation**: Uses `getPostUrl()` helper to respect custom URL prefixes and basePath configuration
4. **Localization**: Uses `resolveLocale()` to handle i18n-aware title and description
5. **User Discovery**: Feed link appears in footer (configurable) and can be embedded in pages via `<rss-feed />` tag
6. **Feed URL Widget**: Interactive component allows users to easily copy the feed URL

All files are properly integrated and tested, with full i18n support for both English and Chinese content.

